Key Match Events: Victor Wembanyama scored 29 points, went 10-of-17 from the field, and added 7 rebounds and 3 blocks in the Spurs' 109-106 win over the Rockets.
Post-Match Reflections: The home crowd chanted 'MVP' as Wembanyama delivered one big play after another.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Rockets' strategy to slow down San Antonio focused heavily on Alperen Sengun and Jabari Smith Jr.
Others: The Spurs built a solid lead, even going up by 22 points before the Rockets tried to claw their way back with a huge fourth quarter.
